The flowering of the red tide extends about 130 miles along the coast from the Pinellas county to the north until the Lee county to the south.
Irregular plots can be found about 10 miles from the coast of Hillsborough County, but in less locations if compared to last week.
Red tide has also been detected in the county of Pasco.
